history.content:
What are you interested in?

--------------

Take both! (I took 188 recently and I'm taking 189 right now.) Don't listen to others who say that "188 is a joke" - it teaches you very useful topics, such as graphical models, reinforcement learning, and HMMs, all of which are important if you are planning to work in the field of AI. 189 is also a great class, and requires more mathematical maturity. You could definitely take both together.

children.subject: 188 is one of those classes that's good to get some easy (in terms of workload, not GPA) stress free cs units. It's pretty much a fluff class since the workload is a joke, so good if you wanna prioritize on your other classes, bad because the assignments don't teach you anything. Keep in mind the exams will wreck you though. I came out of the class feeling like I didn't learn much at all. If you're interested in AI, obviously take the class and then apply for AI related research to do something that's actually fulfilling for your interests.
188 is not particularly relevant to 189. That said, there are other classes that are more important prereqs, as discussed in @2369, @2353.

Is it a good idea to take 189 without taking 188 first? I'm also thinking of taking 189 next semester, but haven't taken 188. I've heard mixed things--some people say you don't need 188 for 189, others say you do. Does anyone have any input on this? Thanks!!

history.content: I know 188 and 189 deal with different material but I have heard some people suggest I should skip taking 188 and just take 189, others have suggested 188 as a must take class. What are your general opinions on this?
history.subject: CS 189 vs 188
